I don't speak Spanish but I'm sure you're right. Then again, I've seen feline very often used in English as a sort of reverse-cutesy term for just a cat, so I think the clue works - as a clue, not dictionary entry.

Interestingly (or not), Polish does not have the noun equivalent of feline. For us a cat is "kot", be it a lion or housecat. The catty adjective is "koci", which derives from "kot."

